<subSubSection id="C31E6567FFDDF6338C693666F8F9FC8A" pageId="25" pageNumber="83" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8BBB36ECFFDDF6338C693666F8F9FC8A" blockId="25.[1397,2605,287,828]" pageId="25" pageNumber="83">
<emphasis id="B970EAFEFFDDF6338C693666F970FD00" bold="true" box="[1399,1749,634,667]" pageId="25" pageNumber="83">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. The Campo-Ma’an Fruit Bat is only known from a very limited number of specimens, and its conservation threats are unknown. The Campo-Ma’an Fruit Bat occurs in Campo Ma’an National Park (
<collectingCountry id="F313767CFFDDF6338FAE36E8F8EBFC8A" box="[1712,1870,756,785]" name="Cameroon" pageId="25" pageNumber="83">Cameroon</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
